verbose_text: We recently analyzed the characteristics and the auditory hazards of impact noise caused by titanium golf driver heads (GDHs), and demonstrated that impact noise generated by the striking of titanium head golf drivers against balls showed a high peak level of approximately 120 A weighted dB (dBA) and a very short duration of less than 200 ms which could be hazardous to those frequently exercise gold in indoor booth [XREF_BIBR].
